name: app.R
content:
# HCR Probe Generator
# - Upload FASTA or paste sequence
# - Region selection slider
# - Sequence map (SVG) of non-overlapping windows
# - QC computed but NOT added as columns
# - Table and CSV contain ONLY: Pool_name, Sequence
# Base R + shiny only (ASCII-safe)

library(shiny)

EXAMPLE_FASTA <- paste0(
    ">EGFP\n",
    "ATGGTGAGCAAGGGCGAGGAGCTGTTCACCGGGGTGGTGCCCATCCTGGTCGAGCTGGACGGCGACGTAAACGG",
    "CCACAAGTTCAGCGTGTCCGGCGAGGGCGAGGGCGATGCCACCTACGGCAAGCTGACCCTGAAGTTCATCTGCA",
    "CCACCGGCAAGCTGCCCGTGCCCTGGCCCACCCTCGTGACCACCCTGACCTACGGCGTGCAGTGCTTCAGCCGC",
    "TACCCCGACCACATGAAGCAGCACGACTTCTTCAAGTCCGCCATGCCCGAAGGCTACGTCCAGGAGCGCACCAT",
    "CTTCTTCAAGGACGACGGCAACTACAAGACCCGCGCCGAGGTGAAGTTCGAGGGCGACACCCTGGTGAACCGCA",
    "TCGAGCTGAAGGGCATCGACTTCAAGGAGGACGGCAACATCCTGGGGCACAAGCTGGAGTACAACTACAACAGC",
    "CACAACGTCTATATCATGGCCGACAAGCAGAAGAACGGCATCAAGGTGAACTTCAAGATCCGCCACAACATCGA",
    "GGACGGCAGCGTGCAGCTCGCCGACCACTACCAGCAGAACACCCCCATCGGCGACGGCCCCGTGCTGCTGCCCG",
    "ACAACCACTACCTGAGCACCCAGTCCGCCCTGAGCAAAGACCCCAACGAGAAGCGCGATCACATGGTCCTGCTG",
    "GAGTTCGTGACCGCCGCCGGGATCACTCTCGGCATGGACGAGCTGTACAAGTAA"
)

# ---------- Minimal helpers ---------------------------------------------------

read_fasta_first <- function(path) {
    lines <- readLines(path, warn = FALSE)
    parse_fasta_text(lines)
}

parse_fasta_text <- function(x) {
    # x can be a character vector of lines or a single string
    if (length(x) == 1L) x <- unlist(strsplit(x, "\n", fixed = TRUE), use.names = FALSE)
    x <- gsub("\r", "", x, fixed = TRUE)
    non_header <- x[substr(x, 1L, 1L) != ">"]
    if (length(non_header) == 0L) stop("No sequence lines found.")
    seq <- toupper(gsub("\\s+", "", paste(non_header, collapse = "")))
    # keep only canonical bases
    seq <- gsub("[^ACGTN]", "", seq, perl = TRUE)
    if (nchar(seq) < 52) stop("Sequence must be at least 52 bases after cleaning.")
    seq
}

rev_comp <- function(s) {
    s <- toupper(s)
    map <- c(A="T", T="A", G="C", C="G", N="N")
    chars <- strsplit(s, "", fixed = TRUE)[[1]]
    rc <- rev(map[chars])
    paste(rc, collapse = "")
}

# Probeset table (extend as needed)
split_init_seqs <- data.frame(
    probeset = c("B1","B2","B3","B4","B5","B7","B9","B10","B11","B13","B14","B15","B17"),
    init_first_half = c("GAGGAGGGCAGCAAACGG","CCTCGTAAATCCTCATCA","GTCCCTGCCTCTATATCT","CCTCAACCTACCTCCAAC","CTCACTCCCAATCTCTAT","CTTCAACCTCCACCTACC","CACGTATCTACTCCACTC","CCTCAAGATACTCCTCTA","CGCTTAGATATCACTCCT","AGGTAACGCCTTCCTGCT","AATGTCAATAGCGAGCGA","CAGATTAACACACCACAA","CGATTGTTTGTTGTGGAC"),
    init_second_half = c("GAAGAGTCTTCCTTTACG","ATCATCCAGTAAACCGCC","CCACTCAACTTTAACCCG","TCTCACCATATTCGCTTC","CTACCCTACAAATCCAAT","TCCAATCCCTACCCTCAC","TCAGCACACTCCCAACCC","CCTACTCGACTACCCTAG","ACGTCGACCACACTCATC","TTATGCTCAACATACAAC","CCCTATATTTCTGCACAG","GGTATCTCGAACACTCTC","GCATGCTAATCGGATGAG"),
    first_spacer  = c("aa","aa","tt","aa","aa","aa","ta","tt","at","ta","aa","tt","aa"),
    second_spacer = c("ta","ta","tt","at","aa","at","at","at","ta","tt","at","aa","ta"),
    stringsAsFactors = FALSE
)

# Sliding 52-nt windows
generate_subseqs <- function(seq) {
    L <- nchar(seq)
    if (L < 52) stop("Sequence must be at least 52 bases.")
    starts <- 1:(L-51)
    ends   <- 52:L
    probe  <- substring(seq, starts, ends)
    data.frame(seqname = "seq1", start = starts, end = ends, probe_seq = probe)
}

# Filter simple repeats: >=5 mono, >=5 di, >=4 tri
complexity_filter <- function(df) {
    keep <- !grepl("(.)\\1{4,}|(..)\\2{4,}|(...)\\3{3,}", df$probe_seq, perl = TRUE)
    df[keep, , drop = FALSE]
}

# Pick non-overlapping windows (greedy by order)
get_non_overlapping <- function(df) {
    res <- df[0,]; last_end <- -Inf
    for (i in seq_len(nrow(df))) {
        if (i == 1 || df$start[i] > last_end) {
            res <- rbind(res, df[i,]); last_end <- df$end[i]
        }
    }
    res$pair_ID <- seq_len(nrow(res))
    res
}

make_fulllength_probes <- function(seq) {
    df <- generate_subseqs(seq)
    df <- complexity_filter(df)
    get_non_overlapping(df)
}

make_split_probes <- function(FL_df, probeset_choice) {
    row <- split_init_seqs[split_init_seqs$probeset == probeset_choice,]
    if (nrow(row) == 0) stop("Selected hairpin pair not found.")
    # 52mer -> 25 + (skip 2) + 25
    p1 <- substring(FL_df$probe_seq, 1, 25)
    p2 <- substring(FL_df$probe_seq, 28, 52)
    probe_1_seq <- vapply(p1, rev_comp, character(1))
    probe_2_seq <- vapply(p2, rev_comp, character(1))
    data.frame(
        seqname = FL_df$seqname,
        probeset = probeset_choice,
        start = FL_df$start, end = FL_df$end,
        odd_ID = paste0(FL_df$pair_ID, ".1"),
        init_first_half = row$init_first_half,
        first_spacer    = row$first_spacer,
        probe_1_seq     = probe_1_seq,
        even_ID         = paste0(FL_df$pair_ID, ".2"),
        probe_2_seq     = probe_2_seq,
        second_spacer   = row$second_spacer,
        init_second_half= row$init_second_half,
        stringsAsFactors = FALSE
    )
}

make_oPools_df <- function(split_df, limit = nrow(split_df)*2) {
    seq_1 <- paste0(split_df$init_first_half, tolower(split_df$first_spacer),  split_df$probe_1_seq)
    seq_2 <- paste0(split_df$probe_2_seq,      tolower(split_df$second_spacer),split_df$init_second_half)
    pool_name <- paste(
        split_df$seqname,
        min(split_df$start), max(split_df$end),
        split_df$probeset,
        paste0(nrow(split_df), "pp"),
        sep = "_"
    )
    out <- data.frame(
        Pool_name = rep(pool_name, 2),
        Sequence  = c(seq_1, seq_2),
        stringsAsFactors = FALSE
    )
    if (nrow(out) > limit) out <- out[seq_len(limit), , drop = FALSE]
    out
}

# QC helpers (kept as attributes, not columns)
gc_percent <- function(s) {
    s <- toupper(s); n <- nchar(s); if (n == 0) return(NA_real_)
    b <- strsplit(s, "", fixed = TRUE)[[1]]
    100 * sum(b %in% c("G","C")) / n
}
tm_wallace <- function(s) {
    s <- toupper(s)
    b <- strsplit(s, "", fixed = TRUE)[[1]]
    A <- sum(b=="A"); T <- sum(b=="T"); G <- sum(b=="G"); C <- sum(b=="C")
    2*(A+T) + 4*(G+C)
}
has_homopolymer <- function(s, k=5){
    grepl("(A{5,}|C{5,}|G{5,}|T{5,})", toupper(s), perl = TRUE)
}

# Build a simple SVG map of non-overlapping windows (ASCII-safe)
build_probe_svg <- function(L, df, offset = 0, width = 900, height = 80, pad = 20){
    scale_x <- function(pos) round(pad + (pos / L) * (width - 2*pad))
    seq_y <- height/2; rect_h <- 16
    
    children <- list(
        tags$line(x1 = pad, y1 = seq_y, x2 = width - pad, y2 = seq_y,
                  stroke = "#334155", `stroke-width` = 2)
    )
    if (!is.null(df) && nrow(df) > 0){
        for (i in seq_len(nrow(df))) {
            x1 <- scale_x(df$start[i])
            x2 <- scale_x(df$end[i])
            children <- append(children, list(
                tags$rect(x = x1, y = seq_y - rect_h/2,
                          width = max(2, x2 - x1), height = rect_h,
                          fill = "#0e7c86", opacity = 0.55, stroke="#0e7c86")
            ))
        }
    }
    ticks <- c(0, .25, .5, .75, 1) * L
    for (t in ticks) {
        tx <- scale_x(t)
        children <- append(children, list(
            tags$line(x1 = tx, y1 = seq_y + 18, x2 = tx, y2 = seq_y + 24, stroke = "#94a3b8"),
            tags$text(x = tx, y = seq_y + 36,
                      style = "font-size:10px; fill:#475569; text-anchor:middle;",
                      round(t + offset))
        ))
    }
    svg <- do.call(
        tagAppendChildren,
        c(list(tags$svg(
            width = width, height = height + 40,
            viewBox = paste("0 0", width, height + 40),
            style="width:100%; max-width:900px; height:auto; background:#f8fafc; border-radius:8px;"
        )), children)
    )
    svg
}

# ---------- UI ----------------------------------------------------------------

ui <- fluidPage(
    titlePanel("Split-initiator HCR V3 Probe Generator"),
    sidebarLayout(
        sidebarPanel(
            radioButtons(
                "input_mode", "Input method",
                choices = c("Upload FASTA" = "file", "Paste sequence / FASTA" = "paste"),
                inline = FALSE
            ),
            conditionalPanel(
                "input.input_mode === 'file'",
                fileInput("fasta_file", "Upload FASTA File", accept = c(".fasta", ".fa"))
            ),
            conditionalPanel(
                "input.input_mode === 'paste'",
                tags$label("Paste sequence (raw bases or FASTA with >header)"),
                textAreaInput("paste_seq", NULL, rows = 8, width = "100%")
            ),
            selectInput("hairpin_pair", "Select Probe Hairpin Pair",
                        choices = split_init_seqs$probeset),
            sliderInput("region", "Analyze region (nt positions)",
                        min = 1, max = 1000, value = c(1, 1000), step = 1),
            numericInput("limit", "Max oligos (rows in CSV)", value = 66, min = 2, step = 2),
            checkboxInput("show_map", "Show sequence map", TRUE),
            actionButton("load_example", "Load example sequence"),
            actionButton("generate", "Generate"),
            downloadButton("download", "Download CSV")
        ),
        mainPanel(
            uiOutput("info"),
            # Show the example image only until "Generate" is clicked
            conditionalPanel("input.generate === 0",
                             tags$figure(
                                 style = "margin:0 0 12px 0;",
                                 tags$img(
                                     src = "hcr_example.png",   # keep the file in www/
                                     alt = "Representative fluorescent in situ hybridization image",
                                     style = "width:50%; height:auto; border-radius:12px; display:block; box-shadow:0 4px 16px rgba(0,0,0,0.08);"
                                 ),
                                 tags$figcaption(
                                     style = "margin-top:6px; color:#64748b; font-size:0.95rem;",
                                     "Representative HCR in situ signal. Signals and images will vary by target and tissue."
                                 )
                             )
            ),
            conditionalPanel("input.show_map === true", uiOutput("seq_map")),
            uiOutput("qc_note"),
            tableOutput("probe_table")
        )
    )
)

# ---------- Server ------------------------------------------------------------

server <- function(input, output, session){
    
    observeEvent(input$load_example, {
        updateRadioButtons(session, "input_mode", selected = "paste")
        updateTextAreaInput(session, "paste_seq", value = EXAMPLE_FASTA)
        L <- nchar(parse_fasta_text(EXAMPLE_FASTA))
        updateSliderInput(session, "region", min = 1, max = L, value = c(1, min(L, 1000)))
        showNotification("eGFP example loaded. Click Generate to run.", type = "message")
    })
    
    probe_data <- eventReactive(input$generate, {
        # Get sequence
        seq <- if (input$input_mode == "file") {
            req(input$fasta_file$datapath); read_fasta_first(input$fasta_file$datapath)
        } else {
            txt <- input$paste_seq; req(nzchar(txt)); parse_fasta_text(txt)
        }
        
        # Fit region slider to sequence and slice subsequence
        isolate({
            L <- nchar(seq)
            start <- max(1, min(input$region[1], L))
            end   <- max(start, min(input$region[2], L))
            updateSliderInput(session, "region", min = 1, max = L, value = c(start, end))
        })
        subseq <- substring(seq, input$region[1], input$region[2])
        
        # Compute full windows -> split -> long output
        full  <- make_fulllength_probes(subseq)
        split <- make_split_probes(full, input$hairpin_pair)
        out   <- make_oPools_df(split, limit = input$limit)
        
        # QC (attributes only; not added as columns)
        qc_gc   <- vapply(out$Sequence, gc_percent,  numeric(1))
        qc_tm   <- vapply(out$Sequence, tm_wallace,  numeric(1))
        qc_flag <- vapply(out$Sequence, has_homopolymer, logical(1))
        
        # Attach attributes for info + map + qc
        attr(out, "seq_len") <- nchar(seq)
        attr(out, "pairs")   <- nrow(split)
        attr(out, "offset")  <- input$region[1] - 1
        attr(out, "full_df") <- list(df = full[, c("start","end","probe_seq")],
                                     seq_used = subseq)
        attr(out, "qc_gc")   <- qc_gc
        attr(out, "qc_tm")   <- qc_tm
        attr(out, "qc_flag") <- qc_flag
        
        out
    })
    
    output$info <- renderUI({
        df <- req(probe_data())
        seq_len <- attr(df, "seq_len"); pairs <- attr(df, "pairs")
        tags$p(class = "text-muted",
               sprintf("Input length: %s nt  |  Non-overlapping probe pairs: %s  |  Rows in table: %s",
                       seq_len, pairs, nrow(df)))
    })
    
    output$seq_map <- renderUI({
        df <- req(probe_data())
        meta <- attr(df, "full_df"); if (is.null(meta)) return(NULL)
        offset <- attr(df, "offset")
        tags$div(
            build_probe_svg(L = nchar(meta$seq_used), df = meta$df, offset = offset),
            tags$p(class="text-muted",
                   sprintf("Showing %d non-overlapping windows across %d nt region.",
                           nrow(meta$df), nchar(meta$seq_used)))
        )
    })
    
    output$qc_note <- renderUI({
        df <- req(probe_data())
        flags <- attr(df, "qc_flag"); n_warn <- sum(flags, na.rm = TRUE)
        if (n_warn > 0) {
            tags$p(class = "text-muted small",
                   sprintf("QC note: %d oligos contain homopolymers (>=5). (Not shown in the IDT file.)", n_warn))
        } else {
            NULL
        }
    })
    
    output$probe_table <- renderTable({
        df <- req(probe_data())
        df[, c("Pool_name","Sequence"), drop = FALSE]
    })
    
    output$download <- downloadHandler(
        filename = function() {
            sprintf("probes_%s_%s.csv", input$hairpin_pair, Sys.Date())
        },
        content = function(file) {
            df <- req(probe_data())
            write.csv(df[, c("Pool_name","Sequence"), drop = FALSE], file, row.names = FALSE)
        }
    )
}

shinyApp(ui, server)
